description:
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a band 6 vacancy to join our team on Burns ICU at Manchester University Foundation Trust Wythenshawe sites busy Regional Adult Burns Centre. The unit has its own intensive care, high dependency and ward level beds running along side our operating theatre and outreach service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a team, we are committed to delivering the highest standards of care whilst meeting the physical, emotional and complex psychosocial needs of our patients. The unit encourages and supports staff development having links with the Critical Care Institute and other educational providers within Greater Manchester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this position it is essential you have 12 months NHS experience and have 3 years ICU skills as a registered nurse. Burns experience is derisible but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking to develop your career and want to be part of our diverse service the please contact us for more information or to organise an informal visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Sue Gibbons, Ward Manager or Sister Sally Holmes on ex 0161 291 6313&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
